# Context for Cursor

This repo is an APP BUILD TOOL, not just the finished product. Grant is using
it as his workbench to build the real pet-song app inside of it.

What that means in practice:

- The core of the workbench is /lab (app/lab/page.tsx + app/api/lab/*):
  a 4-column prompt lab — inferred intake form → editable songwriting prompt
  → generated lyrics (with lint badges) → one-click MiniMax song generation.
  Grant iterates on the lyric-writing prompt here until songs are right.
- lib/lyrics-prompt.ts is the product's core IP. It is intentionally a blank
  shell. Grant authors it himself, testing versions in /lab first. Do not
  fill it in, "improve" it, or restate the JSON output format inside it —
  the machine contract lives in lib/claude.ts (OUTPUT_CONTRACT) and must
  stay there.
- The customer funnel (/ → /create → mock payment → /preview → /song) is the
  MVP being built. Payments (Stripe) and email (Resend) are deliberately
  stubbed: app/api/mock-payment and app/api/mock-upsell are the exact seams
  where real Stripe webhooks go later; app/api/select has the TODO(resend)
  seam. Do not add Stripe or Resend dependencies until asked.
- /dev/test is a quick end-to-end pipeline check with a hardcoded brief.
- /dashboard is the admin view (ADMIN_PASSWORD cookie auth — same auth gates
  the /lab APIs).

Pipeline: Claude (claude-sonnet-4-6, writes lyrics + style prompts, 3 variants)
→ MiniMax music-2.6 (sings them; MINIMAX_MODEL env var, music-2.6-free for
testing) → ffmpeg 45s previews → Supabase Storage (songs-full private,
songs-previews public).

Song length is controlled by lyric line count (MiniMax has no duration
setting) — keep that logic in the prompt/lint layer, not in code.

Stack: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind, Supabase (service-role
client in API routes only), deployed on Vercel. Long-running routes export
maxDuration = 300.
